Title: YOUNG ADULT Trailer 2011 Official [HD]
Comment: While sometimes funny, Young Adult lacks the charm and warmth of Juno. Unrealistic, too. No alcoholic with trichotillomania would look half as good or have half as much hair as Mavis, a sociopath who neglects her devoted dog and caring parents while relentlessly working to destroy a loving family just to satisfy her twisted, delusional desires. Mavis not only clings to her long gone adolescence; she clings to such pure evil that this movie's few humorous moments can't compensate for how unlikable she is. She's as cruel, selfish and uncaring now as she was in high school so we're left wondering what did a great guy like Buddy ever see in her? She's the kind of person who would do the world a favor if she fell down a flight of stairs and broke her neck as everyone, including her dog, would be better off if she was dead. Finally, when there's hope Mavis is motivated to mature into her better self, it's quickly crushed by Matt's sister, Sandra, who's infatuation blinds her to Mavis' many faults. Mavis enthusiastically embraces Sandra's asinine advice to continue being the same (evil) person she's always been. God help anyone like Mavis in real life. Age and alcoholism will quickly ravage the remaining remnants of her physical beauty; the only quality Mavis posseses because she has no heart and no soul.
